<Layout
	title="My Reading"
	description=""
>
	<h3>Why read?</h3>
    <p>
		Reading is important to me. As for most people, the quantity of digital dominates, 
        but I've never forgotten the added quality, sensation, and permanence (as opposed to
        ephemerality and transience) of physical books. Thankfully, I've gotten back into the habit of actually 
        reading the physical books I buy.
	</p>
    <h3>Keeping track</h3>
    <p>
        In the past, I used goodreads to keep a list of book "shelves" and reviews, but that website 
        doesn't seem to be maintained much. So I've decided to maintain my own list of books and 
        reviews, for now.
    </p>

    <h3>Gifting and sharing books</h3>
    <!-- <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}> -->
    <div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'flex-start' }}>
        <Image src={bookSharingPhoto} alt="Sharing books in the neighborhood" width="150" style={{ marginRight: '20px' }} />
        <p>
            Some neighborhoods have a box which works as a "little library" where people can both leave books
            for others to take, and take books that others have left for them. I appreciate this as a way to share books
            etc.
        </p>
    </div>


    <h3>Is it good?</h3>
